The paper deals with the complexity of identity testing of noncommutative rational functions, which is a fundamental problem in computational complexity theory. The paper also focuses on a specific subclass of rational expressions, namely those of inversion height one in the free group algebra. This suggests that the paper may be relevant to several subfields of computer science, including computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), logic in computer science (cs.LO), graph theory (cs.GT), and automata and formal languages (cs.AC).
